      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Impossible to go past MORGANA (7) who is a lightly raced filly well back in class. Finished eighth in the Group 2 Armanasco Stakes fresh then 10th in the Group 3 Peter Le Grand last time. Fitter and facing a huge class drop. Only other try at 1400m was only a few lengths away in stakes class. Gets chance to show best. INHERENTLY (3) is an honest type who resumed with a fast finishing third at Ballarat over a mile. Fitter and will be winding up late. THE DAILY PLANET (8) turned in an eye-catching run last time out over 1600m at Colac, charging home from well back to finish a long neck away in second. Another hard to hold out. DIAMOND WAR (2) turned things around last start and landed the prize by a neck over 1400m at Horsham. Down in weight and will take catching again. INTO YOU (5) is fitter and will be hard to beat this easier grade.",
